I89. Definitions for this subchapter

I11In this subchapter_

I12(1) ``Commission'' means Securities and Exchange Commission;

I12(2) ``customer'' includes_

I13(A) entity with whom a person deals as principal or agent and that has a claim against such person on account of a security received, acquired, or held by such person in the ordinary course of such person's business as a stockbroker, from or for the securities account or accounts of such entity_

I14(i) for safekeeping;

I14(ii) with a view to sale;

I14(iii) to cover a consummated sale;

I14(iv) pursuant to a purchase;

I14(v) as collateral under a security agreement; or

I14(vi) for the purpose of effecting registration of transfer; and

Q04

I13(B) entity that has a claim against a person arising out of_

I14(i) a sale or conversion of a security received, acquired, or held as specified in subparagraph (A) of this paragraph; or

I14(ii) a deposit of cash, a security, or other property with such person for the purpose of purchasing or selling a security;

Q04

I12(3) ``customer name security'' means security_

I13(A) held for the account of a customer on the date of the filing of the petition by or on behalf of the debtor;

I13(B) registered in such customer's name on such date or in the process of being so registered under instructions from the debtor; and

I13(C) not in a form transferable by delivery on such date;

Q04

I12(4) ``customer property'' means cash, security, or other property, and proceeds of such cash, security, or property, received, acquired, or held by or for the account of the debtor, from or for the securities account of a customer_

I13(A) including_

I14(i) property that was unlawfully converted from and that is the lawful property of the estate;

I14(ii) a security held as property of the debtor to the extent such security is necessary to meet a net equity claim of a customer based on a security of the same class and series of an issuer;

I14(iii) resources provided through the use or realization of a customer's debit cash balance or a debit item includible in the Formula for Determination of Reserve Requirement for Brokers and Dealers as promulgated by the Commission under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934; and

I14(iv) other property of the debtor that any applicable law, rule, or regulation requires to be set aside or held for the benefit of a customer, unless including such property as customer property would not significantly increase customer property; but

Q04

I13(B) not including_

I14(i) a customer name security delivered to or reclaimed by a customer under section 751 of this title; or

I14(ii) property to the extent that a customer does not have a claim against the debtor based on such property;

Q04

I12(5) ``margin payment'' means payment or deposit of cash, a security, or other property, that is commonly known to the securities trade as original margin, initial margin, maintenance margin, or variation margin, or as a mark-to-market payment, or that secures an obligation of a participant in a securities clearing agency;

