I89. Conversion or dismissal

I11(a) The debtor may convert a case under this chapter to a case under chapter 7 of this title at any time. Any waiver of the right to convert under this subsection is unenforceable.

I11(b) On request of the debtor at any time, if the case has not been converted under section 706 or 1112 of this title, the court shall dismiss a case under this chapter. Any waiver of the right to dismiss under this subsection is unenforceable.

I11(c) On request of a party in interest, and after notice and a hearing, the court may dismiss a case under this chapter for cause, including_

I12(1) unreasonable delay, or gross mismanagement, by the debtor that is prejudicial to creditors;

I12(2) nonpayment of any fees and charges required under chapter 123 of title 28;

I12(3) failure to file a plan timely under section 1221 of this title;

I12(4) failure to commence making timely payments required by a confirmed plan;

I12(5) denial of confirmation of a plan under section 1225 of this title and denial of a request made for additional time for filing another plan or a modification of a plan;

I12(6) material default by the debtor with respect to a term of a confirmed plan;

I12(7) revocation of the order of confirmation under section 1230 of this title, and denial of confirmation of a modified plan under section 1229 of this title;

I12(8) termination of a confirmed plan by reason of the occurrence of a condition specified in the plan;

I12(9) continuing loss to or diminution of the estate and absence of a reasonable likelihood of rehabilitation; and

I12(10) failure of the debtor to pay any domestic support obligation that first becomes payable after the date of the filing of the petition.

