I80ÿ1A1512

I89. Participation of a foreign representative in a case under this title

I11Upon recognition of a foreign proceeding, the foreign representative in the recognized proceeding is entitled to participate as a party in interest in a case regarding the debtor under this title.

I53(Added Pub. L. 109ÿ098, title VIII, ÿ1A801(a), Apr. 20, 2005, 119 Stat. 138.)

I80ÿ1A1513

I89. Access of foreign creditors to a case under this title

I11(a) Foreign creditors have the same rights regarding the commencement of, and participation in, a case under this title as domestic creditors.

I11(b)(1) Subsection (a) does not change or codify present law as to the priority of claims under section 507 or 726, except that the claim of a foreign creditor under those sections shall not be given a lower priority than that of general unsecured claims without priority solely because the holder of such claim is a foreign creditor.

I11(2)(A) Subsection (a) and paragraph (1) do not change or codify present law as to the allowability of foreign revenue claims or other foreign public law claims in a proceeding under this title.

I11(B) Allowance and priority as to a foreign tax claim or other foreign public law claim shall be governed by any applicable tax treaty of the United States, under the conditions and circumstances specified therein.

